# Create a 2x2 grid of subplots
fig, axs = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(12, 10))  # Adjust figsize as needed

# Adjust spacing between subplots and top of figure to make room for the big title
fig.subplots_adjust(top=0.9)

# Plot 1
ph_da_ac.plot(ax=axs[0, 0])
axs[0, 0].set_title("Soil pH (60100 cm depth)")

# Plot 2
ph_fuzz_ac.plot(ax=axs[0, 1])  # Replace with your actual data
axs[0, 1].set_title("pH Fuzzy Suitability Score")

# Plot 3
precip_mean_da_ac.plot(ax=axs[1, 0])  # Replace with your actual data
axs[1, 0].set_title("Mean Annual Precipitation in Sheyenne National Grassland")

# Plot 4
precip_min_fuzz_ac.plot(ax=axs[1, 1])  # Replace with your actual data
axs[1, 1].set_title("Minimum Precipitation Fuzzy Logic Score")

# Add one title for the entire figure
fig.suptitle("Sheyenne National Grassland Cold & Dry Scenario", fontsize=16)

plt.show()
